cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.IT, cs.LG

This paper focuses on the development and evaluation of a computer-assisted multi-modal training system for medical students to improve their clinical examination skills in relation to abdominal palpation. The paper employs user-centered design methods and involves medical professionals in the design and assessment stages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). 

The paper also involves the use of technology (computer-based methods) to assess the performance of medical students, which suggests the possibility of belonging to sub-categories such as cs.CY (Computational Geometry), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.IT (Information Theory). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to capture and model best practice models for each palpation task, which suggests the possibility of belonging to sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
